import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='u', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the range of values for the 'u' field?", wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['u'].min():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['u'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['v'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the 'v' field?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
